posts.title: I had an abortion conversation the other day with cheer moms.
posts.content:
So, I was at my child's tumbling practice (in the private sector, we don't touch government schools). There's 2 moms I'd call acquaintances, but we chat often while the kids practice.

I'm not one to bring up politics with acquaintances. And we're in a room with about a half dozen other parents that can hear our conversation.

Anyway the one mom brings up the debate. She brings up eating dogs and I pointed out how over 20k migrants were dropped into a town of 50k. The cultures just are not going to mesh in that volume. She made a "hmm" face and moved on.

Then, she moves on and brings up the post birth abortion point. She talks about how they're not killing babies after birth... And I point out how 8 babies in Montana died after botch abortions. What would you call that? "They're not just leaving them to die" but I kept pushing how these babies were born and literally left to die.

We went back and forth for most of the class. Everything stayed calm and civil. But there were a ton of issues she had no idea about like planned parenthood selling baby part, states with little to no restrictions, ect. I talked about how abortion is taking a life. She talked about "choice" and the 1% of cases.

Anyway, we landed on agree to disagree. And a note from her with " what about the life of the mom" and response from me saying "but we're not talking about a life, there're 2 lives in this situation ". I hope she researches some of the points I brought up.

I just want to remind you all to stand your ground and talk more politics; keep it civil. We're in this situation because we were taught not to talk politics.

To the other lady pedes: please speak up on this topic. The left thinks it's "all men" who want to ban abortions. We need to have these conversations more often.
